place.name: INNERWICK
place.gazetteerText: Innerwick, coast par. and vil. with ry. sta., E. Haddingtonshire, 13,157 ac., pop. 777; P.O.; the sta. is 1¼ mile E. of the vil. and 4½ miles SE. of Dunbar; 1 mile E. of vil., on the edge of a precipitous glen, are the rums of Innerwick Castle, burned by the Duke of Somerset, 1548. (In 1887, John Bartholomew's Gazetteer of the British Isles)
